definition.p:
    Let X be a set and let \mathcal{A}\subseteq
      \mathcal{P}(X), that is, \mathcal{A} is a set of
  subsets of X. We say that \mathcal{A} is
  an algebra of subsets of X if the following
  conditions hold.

    X\in \mathcal{A}

    \text{if } A\in \mathcal{A}, \text{ then }(X \setminus A)\in
	\mathcal{A} 

    \text{if }A,B \in \mathcal{A}, 
    \text{ then }(A\cup B)\in \mathcal{A}
